# Copy to ftp.env (gitignored) for local reference only — CI uses GitHub Actions secrets.
#
# In GitHub: Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret
#
# FTP_SERVER       = Host from Namecheap (often ftp.yourdomain.com or server hostname from cPanel)
# FTP_USERNAME     = Full FTP username from Namecheap (may include @domain.com)
# FTP_PASSWORD     = FTP account password
# FTP_SERVER_DIR   = Remote folder for the static site — MUST end with /
#                    Example for Next basePath /bootcamp:  /public_html/bootcamp/
#
# If FTPS fails in CI (TLS/certificate issues), edit .github/workflows/deploy-ftp.yml
# and set protocol: ftp (not recommended on public Wi‑Fi) or try ftps-legacy per host docs.
FTP_USERNAME=developer@dlthub.org
FTP_SERVER=ftp.dlthub.org
FTP_PASSWORD=*ONLYadmin99#
FTP_SERVER_DIR=/public_html/bootcamp/